  "poem": {
    "content": "The early sun, an oval stain,\nbehind the fading indigo.\nA bachelor dawn, recalling rain,\nupon the oyster's echo.\n\nNo tourist yet disturbs the shore,\nwhere grains of sand like dreams reside.\nAn infant wave, then nothing more,\nas carbon ghosts begin to hide.\n\nWe work, a project yet untold,\nto dish out futures, brave and bright.\nA secret story to unfold,\nlike foil reflecting back the light.\n\nFrom output small, ideas grow,\nWe must develop what is sown -\nthough some may see just empty show,\na wasteland they have always known.\n\nThe world behind is yesterday,\nWe dream a new dawn every day.\nNew worlds will rise, we work to show,\nthese rising worlds will start to grow.",
